"{\"uid\": \"myrepublica.nagariknetwork.com-news-nepali-athletes-leave-for-33rd-summer-paris-olympics\", \"text\": \"Subscribe Now  KATHMANDU, July 19: Nepali athletes who are participating in the 33rd Summer Paris Olympics have been given a farewell. President Ram Chandra Paudel conveyed his best wishes to all the players at a program held at Sheetal Niwas on Friday.  The President urged the players to compete in all sports with utmost dedication, stating that sports are the best way to make the nation known in the international arena.  President Paudel expressed his belief that the participation of athletes in the Summer Paris Olympics would be prestigious for the country. He motivated all the athletes to participate in all sports with utmost enthusiasm and dedication.  The president handed the national flag to Nepal Sports Council Member Secretary Tanka Lal Ghising.  The Minister for Youth and Sports, Tejulal Chaudhary, urged the athletes to participate with high morale and wished them success.  Minister for Youth and Sports, Chaudhary, president of Nepal Olympic Committee Jeevan Ram Shrestha, athletes, and coaches participating in the 33rd Summer Paris Olympics were present on the occasion.    Ballot Box Revolt: What RSP's breakthrough victory...  Warning, Threat or Opportunity? Nepal's major part...  Granary in crisis: Water politics leave Madhesh pa...  \\\"China stands ready to work with Nepal to carry forward the traditional friendship, deepen practical cooperation and advance bilateral relations\\\", read the statement.  Building Nepal's Digital Future  Fuel shortages in Nepal: A hidden threat to health a...  Second Innings of Balen and Gagan  Who will become Balen's climate pilot?  Three \\\"S\\\" factors-sulabhata (availability), sangat (peer influence), and siko (imitation)-are driving Madhesh's youth toward drug addiction.<...  Three \\\"S\\\" factors-sulabhata (availability), sangat (peer influence), and siko (imitation)-are driving Madhesh's youth tow